article.headline: Lehigh 65, Holy Cross 58
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- Marquis Hall hit all 10 of his free throws and finished with 23 points, and Lehigh rallied in the second half to beat Holy Cross 65-58 on Friday night. Bryan White scored 14 points and Rob Keefer 11 for Lehigh (14-14, 7-7 Patriot League), which rallied from a six-point halftime deficit. Tim Clifford scored 25 points to lead Holy Cross (15-13, 5-9), which lost its third straight league game. Colin Cunningham chipped in with 15 points. Lehigh shot 10-for28 in the first half and made just two of 10 shots from 3-point range. But the Mountain Hawks found their range in the second half, shooting 10-for-25 from the field and 17-for-23 from the line to complete the come-from-behind victory. Lehigh's subs outscored Holy Cross' 17-2, and the Mountain Hawks outscored their opponent 11-3 on second-chance points.
